1 A JOINT RESOLUTION
2 PROPOSING TO AMEND ARTICLE 4, SECTION 10 OF THE CONSTITUTION
3 OF NEW MEXICO TO ALLOW LEGISLATIVE COMPENSATION THAT IS
4 LIMITED TO THE MEDIAN HOUSEHOLD INCOME FOR NEW MEXICO, TO
5 REQUIRE LEGISLATIVE COMPENSATION TO BE REDUCED IF THE MEDIAN
6 HOUSEHOLD INCOME FOR NEW MEXICO FALLS, TO ALLOW LEGISLATIVE
7 COMPENSATION TO BE INCREASED ONLY IF THE MEDIAN HOUSEHOLD
8 INCOME FOR NEW MEXICO RISES AND TO PROVIDE FOR DELAYED
9 IMPLEMENTATION.
10
11 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF NEW MEXICO:
12 SECTION 1. It is proposed to amend Article 4, Section
13 10 of the constitution of New Mexico to read:
14 "A. Each member of the legislature is entitled to
15 receive:
16 (1) per diem at the internal revenue service
17 per diem rate for the city of Santa Fe for each day's
18 attendance during each session of the legislature and the
19 internal revenue service standard mileage rate for each mile
20 traveled in going to and returning from the seat of
21 government by the usual traveled route, once each session as
22 defined by Article 4, Section 5 of this constitution;
23 (2) per diem expense and mileage at the same
24 rates as provided in Paragraph (1) of this subsection for
25 service at meetings required by legislative committees HJR 5/a
Page 1

1 established by the legislature to meet in the interim between
2 sessions; and
3 (3) compensation as provided by law for
4 legislative service in an amount equal to the annual median
5 household income for New Mexico as initially determined and
6 adjusted thereafter by the rise or fall of the median
7 household income for New Mexico.
8 B. The provisions of Paragraph (3) of Subsection A
9 of this section are effective beginning with members seated
10 and sworn in for the fifty-ninth legislature."
11 SECTION 2. The amendment proposed by this resolution
12 shall be submitted to the people for their approval or
13 rejection at the next general election or at any special
14 election prior to that date that may be called for that
15 purpose. HJR 5/a
